  "prompt": "How did Albert Einstein treat his disability?",
  "response": "Albert Einstein is often inaccurately described as having a disability, particularly a learning disability or a developmental disorder like dyslexia or Asperger's syndrome. However, there is no concrete historical evidence to support these claims. \n\nEinstein had been a late talker as a child, which has led to much speculation, but he did not have a diagnosed learning disability during his lifetime. He was able to succeed academically in his later years, despite facing some challenges in the traditional education system due to his non-conformist approach to learning.\n\nIf you have any specific instance or condition you are referring to, please provide more details, and I would be happy to assist further.",
